       <h5>Diviso Fondos<h6>June 2015 - August 2015 | Lima, Peru</h6></h5>
       <hr>
        <p>Following my freshman year, I interned in the Sales and Trading division of Diviso Fondos, an Investment Company in Peru. It was my first exposure to the financial world and I learned way more than I expected.</p>
        <p>I was in charge of elaborating and analyzing daily and monthly reports related to the performance of the mutual funds. I used these reports to generate presentations that were used by the CEO at Board meetings. I also assisted the porfolio managers at the trading desk in their day-to-day transactions by using a Bloomberg terminal, gaining a lot of experience in the field.</p><br/>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-4">

        <h5>Duodecim<h6>April 2014 - August 2014 | Lima, Peru</h6></h5>
        <hr>

        <p>After finishing the IB Diploma, I attended college in Lima for a semester (where studied Industrial Engineering in order to try something different from what I was going to study at Notre Dame) and also started Duodecim with a group of college students in order to provide funds for service projects organized by the Church.</p>
        <p>Besides helping school kids improve their grades and understanding of several subjects, we also donated our incomes to undertake social projects. I gained experience as a tutor and also organized activities in poor communities, especially with young kids.</p><br/>

      </div>

      <div class="col-md-4">

        <h5>Ladrillos Fortes<h6>January 2014 - April 2014 | Lima, Peru</h6></h5>
        <hr>

        <p>Ladrillos Fortes is a Peruvian brick company with factories in four different cities in Peru. I worked as a Sales and Marketing Assistant, and my main duty was to help the division unify information accross the Sales, Marketing and Production Departments to optimize the sales of ceramic bricks.</p>
        <p>This was to be achieved by reducing the amount of remaining stock and by fulfilling customer orders in time, so we had to improve the planning strategy. I also researched new markets by doing one-on-one conversations, phone calls, surveys and visiting retailers.</p>

