       <div class="col-md-4">

        <h5>SIBC International Case Study<h6>October 2015 | Sao Paulo, Brazil</h6></h5>
        <hr>

        <p>During Fall Break of my sophomore year, I traveled with a delegation of seven other Notre Dame students to Brazil to participate in a program with workshops, lectures, and cultural immersion, as well as a case study with students from the University of Campinas.</p>
        <p>It was a great opportunity to work on an international topic with students from diverse backgrounds and to develop global business knowledge and skills. I learned in depth about Brazil's socio-economic situation from the perspective of students, professors, tour guides, and even from the taxi drivers (with whom I got to practice my Portuguese as well!).</p><br/>

      </div>

      <div class="col-md-4">

        <h5>Round Square International Conference<h6>2012 | Nairobi, Kenya</h6></h5>
        <hr>

        <p>My senior year in high school, I attended a conference held in Nairobi with around 300 delegates from around the world. Before attending the actual conference, we went to Mombasa (a beach nearby) and we also went on a safari. This made my first time in Africa an amazing experience.</p>
        <p>The theme of the conference was "No existence without coexistence", which raised awareness of Africa's socio-political issues. I stayed in the house of Kenyian students, and attended several workshops where we discussed our different views of topics related to the theme. We also helped build school classrooms for poor children.</p>

